sp.p:
And now Sirrah, all o' the ſudden, you are unfit for State-affairs;
come, come Sirrah, you are a Villain, have turn'd Cat in Pan;
and are a Tory.

Now ſhall I be wedg'd in, between the old Fool and the young,
by the heavy Beetle of this Poem, and have no opportunity with my
charming Florio, when he comes I'll lay away the Beetle;

Her ſide, that is her part o'th' Court?—her Apartments;
thou think'ſt I'm a raw Courtier; no, Sir, I know Court
Phraſes.

Now wou'd I give ten pound to know which of us two
is mad; if I were ſure he were mad, I'd run and beg him preſently;
but the danger is, leſt I be beg'd my ſelf.
